        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 20 at 7:41PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 740 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Southside in Independence County, or 8 miles southwest of Batesville,
moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Charlotte...                      Salado...
Gainesboro...                     Southside in Independence Count...
Desha...                          Batesville...
Cave City...                      Pfeiffer...
Locust Grove...                   Moorefield...
Hutchinson...                     Almond...
Sulphur Rock...                   Bethesda...
Sandtown...                       Concord...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for north central
Arkansas. A Tornado Watch also remains in effect until midnight CDT
for north central Arkansas.</instruction>
